owl:Ontology.dc:title: SAQI : an ontology to model Social Air Quality
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: Ontology to model Social Air Quality

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The WGS84 altitude of a SpatialThing (decimal meters above the local reference ellipsoid).
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: altitude

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The subject matter of the content.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: about

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: accountId

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: additionalName

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: additionalType

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: affiliation

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An alias for the item.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: alternateName

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: areaServed

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: availableAtOrFrom

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: confirmationNumber

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A season that is part of the media series.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: containsSeason

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: contentLocation

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: course

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: deliveryMethod

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A description of the item.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: description

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: disambiguatingDescription

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: duns

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: duration

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: eligibleRegion

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: entertainmentBusiness

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: episode

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: exerciseCourse

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: flightNumber

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: foodEstablishment

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: foodEvent

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: fromLocation

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: globalLocationNumber

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: gtin12

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: gtin13

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: gtin14

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: gtin8

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: hasPart

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A contact location for a person's residence.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: homeLocation

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of [[Thing]], such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#identifierBg) for more details.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: identifier

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: image

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: ingredients

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The object that helped the agent perform the action. E.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: instrument

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: isPartOf

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The ISBN of the book.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: isbn

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: issn

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: language

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: leiCode

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: loanTerm

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: location

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An associated logo.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: logo

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: mainEntity

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: memberOf

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The name of the item.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: name

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The identifier of the transaction.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: orderNumber

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The episode to which this clip belongs.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: partOfEpisode

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The season to which this episode belongs.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: partOfSeason

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The series to which this episode or season belongs.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: partOfSeries

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: partOfTVSeries

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A photograph of this place.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: photo

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: productID

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: query

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: recipe

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: recipeIngredient

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: sameAs

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A season in a media series.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: season

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: serialNumber

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: sku

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: spatialCoverage

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: sportsActivityLocation

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: sportsEvent

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: supply

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: taxID

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: toLocation

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: tool

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: vehicleIdentificationNumber

owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A contact location for a person's place of work.
owl:AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: workLocation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Any representatives of a particular Institution. e.g. director of a ngo.
Connects a segment to the point it ends at.
An organization giving information to people, e.g. government running an awareness campaign on pollution.
This property links air pollution literacy of a person, that value could be qualitative assesment in the form of data property of AirPollutionLiteracy.
Relating the trajectory to each of its points.
Relating the trajectory to each of its segments.
Anything that has a trajectory can use this property to connect it to the trajectory instance
Relates one point to the immediately following point in the sequence.
Connects a segment to the point it starts from.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
Uniquely identified by lat/long/alt. i.e.
spaciallyIntersects(P1, P2) :- lat(P1, LAT), long(P1, LONG), alt(P1, ALT), lat(P2, LAT), long(P2, LONG), alt(P2, ALT).
sameThing(P1, P2) :- type(P1, Point), type(P2, Point), spaciallyIntersects(P1, P2).
A point, typically described using a coordinate system relative to Earth, such as WGS84.
A point, typically described using a coordinate system relative to Earth, such as WGS84.

Uniquely identified by lat/long/alt. i.e.
spaciallyIntersects(P1, P2) :- lat(P1, LAT), long(P1, LONG), alt(P1, ALT), lat(P2, LAT), long(P2, LONG), alt(P2, ALT).
sameThing(P1, P2) :- type(P1, Point), type(P2, Point), spaciallyIntersects(P1, P2).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: point

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Anything with spatial extent, i.e. size, shape, or position. e.g. people, places, bowling balls, as well as abstract areas like cubes.
Anything with spatial extent, i.e. size, shape, or position. e.g. people, places, bowling balls, as well as abstract areas like cubes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SpatialThing

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An agent (eg. person, group, software or physical artifact).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A person.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Person

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Organization

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Place

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This concept describes the air pollution literacy ofthe people in a locality. We assess this by asking questions18to the people related to their awareness of AQI and air pollution in general. The AirPollutionLiteracy concept has the data properties has AQILiteracy, hasAirPollutionGraphic-Literacy, hasParticulateMatterLiteracy and hasAQIColorLiteracy.
Sensors maintained by Central Pollution Control Board (CPCB), India
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CPCB sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents streams which carry pollutants to a particular place.

This concept is a subclass of the Indirect Contributor concept and represents the air, water, and other kinds of streams flowing into or out of aparticular place. It is linked to theTrajectory concept through the hasTrajectoryproperty. Carriers are generally observed to affect the concentration of pollutants at a particular place and are important in modeling pollutants. To represent the pollutants that might be carried through a trajectory, the Carrier concept is linked to thePollutant concept by the carries Pollutant property.
Government having authority over entire country.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Central Government

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Thermal power plants using coal as source.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Coal based power plant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Any combustion event which may lead to pollution; incomplete combustion is responsible for particulate pollutation which is usually carried out to for burning crops and waste.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Combustion

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Contributor is a subclass of sosa:FeatureOfInterest allowing us to record observations of the contributors, Contributor can either be a contaminant particle, i.e.Pollutant or it could be a Carrier that transports a Pollutant
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Contributor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Crob burning is usually done to clear the fields after harvest and to dispose lefteover stubble. This process releases particle pollution in the air.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Crop burning

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Can also include things like awareness about air quality, most common mode of transportation, etc.
Will capture things like education level, majority types of jobs
Thermal power plants using diesel as source.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Diesel based power plant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents concepts which directly represent pollution. For example the concentration of pollutants at a particular spatio-temporal point.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Direct contributor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Dust particles from construction, waste burning, traffic and industries
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dust

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ending point of a trajectory
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ending point

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Thermal power plants using natural gas as source.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gas based power plant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Primary pollutants that exists in gaseous form
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Gaseous pollutant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A group people that conduct policy, action and affairs of a state or country.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Government

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Hydrocarbons are responsible for generating ozone as a secondary pollutants.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Hydrocarbon

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents concepts which indirectly contribute to pollution of a place. These do not directly represent pollution but have properties which can affect the pollution, for example by changing the concentration of pollutants at a spatio-temporal point.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Indirect contributor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Organizations that are not government such as Schools, NGOs.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Institutions

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Institutions which are against air pollution
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Institutions against Air Pollution

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A smaller level government having authority over towns/villages/regions.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Local Government

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Local sensors maintained by Social Air quality Index (SAQI) team at XXXXX
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Local Sensor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Meterological characterstics
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Meterological characteristic

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Local level Governments having authority over towns, cities or villages.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Municipal Government

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents pollution on natural resources. Which means the pollution that affects natural resources like air, water, land, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Natural resource pollution

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents pollution which does not represent natural resource. Examples include, sound, light, space debris, radioactive pollution, thermal pollution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Non natural resource pollution

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Oxides of carbon has an observable property CarbonMonoOxideConcentraition (CO)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Oxides of carbon

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Oxides of Nitrogen has observable properties NitrogenDiOxideConcentration (NO2) , NitrogenMonoOxideConcentration (NO) , NitrogenOxideConcentration (NOx)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Oxides of nitrogen

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Oxides of Suplhur has observable property SulphurDioxideConcentration (SO2)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Oxides of sulphur

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ozone forms in sunlight and interaction of various primary pollutants such as hydrocarbons and oxides of nitrogen.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ozone

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A mixture of solid and liquid particles in the air. If the size of these particles is smaller than 10 micrometer, they can get deep into our lungs causing health effects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Particulate matter

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This concept captures the perception of an individual with regard to the level of air pollution in their local neighbourhood and the city.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Perception

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents various pollutants which contaminate the environment and directly represnt/contribute to pollution. Additionally a carrier's trajecectory point may pick up pollutants from a spatio-temporal point, in which case, it is represented by the sub-property carriesPollutant.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pollutant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Pollutant generators are events that generate pollution, such as crop burning, power plants, waste burning and dusty weather. It is related to the saqi:Perception class in the Ethnography module, indicating the perception of people on the severity of pollution concentration in a specific area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pollutant generator

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represnents the notion of Pollution which includes observation of pollutants at spatio-temporal points or the contributors to the pollution which may be spatio-temporal in nature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pollution

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Power plants generate usually generate green house gases in huge amounts, but are also responsible for Air pollution generators such as NO2, SO2 and CO.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Power plant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Standards for pollution levels, e.g. CPCB sets PM 2.5 annual average standard at 40 microgram per m^3.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Prescribed standard for pollutant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Primary pollutants are emitted directly from a source. Such as Particulate Matter, SO2, CO, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Primary pollutant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Secondary pollutants are not emitted directly from a source, but are produced from interaction of primary pollutants in the atmosphere
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Secondary pollutant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Starting point of a trajectory
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Starting point

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Power plants converts heat energy into electricity using steam turbines.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Thermal Power Plant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a trajectory of points. Examples include drainage/sewage trajectory or air stream trajectory.
A collection of spatio-temporal points represents a trajectory
A subset of spatio-temporal trajectory points represent a TrajectorySegment
Waste burning is done for the purpose of disposing waste in dense populated areas. This process releases particle pollutants in the air.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Waste burning

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Wind characterstics
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Wind characteristic

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Atmospheric pressure measured in bar. linked to sosa:ObservableProperty saqi:AtmosphericPressure
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Atmospheric pressure

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents the amount of clouds covering the atmosphere measured in unit Okta
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cloud cover

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The temprature at which the atmosphere reaches 100% relative humidity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dew point temprature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Amount of water in atmosphere. Linked to sosa:ObservableProperty saqi:RelativeHumidity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Humidity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Amount of rain, snow or hail that falls to the ground, measured in millimetres where 1 mm corresponds to 1 liter of water per 1 m^2 area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Precipitation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Solar irradiance captures the output of light enery from the sun, measured in W as the energy falling onto the surface per unit of time, per area.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Solar irradiance

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Ambient temprature at surface, measured in Celsius or Fahrenheit
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Temprature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: One-word description of the observed weather condition
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Weather condition

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use [[valueReference]] to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR") instead of including [ambiguous symbols](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dollar_sign#Currencies_that_use_the_dollar_or_peso_sign) such as '$' in the value.

Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.
The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:
1.) *id-value* URL references - uses *id-value* of an element in the page being annotated. The simplest use of *speakable* has (potentially relative) URL values, referencing identified sections of the document concerned.
2.) CSS Selectors - addresses content in the annotated page, e.g. via class attribute. Use the [[cssSelector]] property.
3.) XPaths - addresses content via XPaths (assuming an XML view of the content). Use the [[xpath]] property.
For more sophisticated markup of speakable sections beyond simple ID references, either CSS selectors or XPath expressions to pick out document section(s) as speakable. For this we define a supporting type, [[SpeakableSpecification]] which is defined to be a possible value of the *speakable* property.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in [ISO 8601 time interval format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_intervals). In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content, e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode, may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".
Open-ended date ranges can be written with ".." in place of the end date. For example, "2015-11/.." indicates a range beginning in November 2015 and with no specified final date. This is tentative and might be updated in future when ISO 8601 is officially updated.
